    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"394803\">Jared green</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/accessing.20the.20source.20case.20during.20induction/near/502098248\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>theorem t  (n : List a) (hn : n ≠ []): p n</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is saying that if you have a list, and it's not empty, then any property holds for it. This seems clearly false to me, so you probably won't be able to find a proof for it.</p>",
